Package org.cloudgraph.query.expr

Contains functionality to impose a binary expression tree structure over the underlying query model capable of modeling and evaluating complex binary and unary logical, relational and arithmetic query expressions under various contexts.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ArithmeticBinaryExpr
    Represents an expression composed of two parts or terms joined by an arithmetic operator.
    BinaryExpr
    Represents an expression composed of two parts or terms.
    EvaluationContext
    Base interface providing context information passed to an expression syntax tree.
    Expr
    Base interface representing a query expression.
    ExprAssembler
    A factory oriented interface used to create various expression implementations.
    ExprVisitor
    Expression visitor pattern client interface.
    LogicalBinaryExpr
    Represents an expression composed of two parts or terms joined by a logical operator.
    RelationalBinaryExpr
    Represents an expression composed of two parts or terms joined by a relational operator.
    Term
    Base interface representing any query term within an expression.
    UnaryExpr
    Represents an expression composed of one term.
    WildcardBinaryExpr
    Represents an expression composed of two parts or terms joined by a wildcard operator.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    DefaultBinaryExpr
    Contains default functionality for query expressions composed of two parts or terms, including a visitor traversal implementation.
    DefaultBinaryExprTreeAssembler
    A binary expression tree assembler which constructs an operator precedence map, then visits (traverses) the given predicate expression syntax tree depth-first using an adapted shunting-yard algorithm and assembles a resulting binary tree structure.
    DefaultExpr
    Default behavior for query expressions.
    DefaultLogicalBinaryExpr
    Contains default functionality for logical binary query expressions.
    DefaultRelationalBinaryExpr
    Contains default functionality for relational binary query expressions.
    DefaultWildcardBinaryExpr
    Contains default functionality for wildcard binary query expressions.
    ExpresionVisitorSupport
    Contains logic related to query expression processing.
    ExprPrinter
    Simple visitor client which creates a "printable" representation of a binary expression tree for debugging purposes.
    Operator
    Encapsulates a single operator and associated precedence evaluation and other logic.

Package org.cloudgraph.query.expr Description

Contains functionality to impose a binary expression tree structure over the underlying query model capable of modeling and evaluating complex binary and unary logical, relational and arithmetic query expressions under various contexts.
